title: Female Head
description:
Terra cotta female head probably of Athena. Helmet on head with hair indicated between edge of helmet and face. Head made as a separate piece. Cast hollow in two part mold. 
Condition: General condition good. Top of helmet missing. Nose chipped.
credit_line: Gift of Evangeline Wilbour Blashfield, Theodora Wilbour, and Victor Wilbour honoring the wishes of their mother, Charlotte Beebe Wilbour, as a memorial to their father, Charles Edwin Wilbour
